Attribute.name: material
Attribute.desc: Material of the Lateral Load-Resisting System

AtomsGroup.name: height_ground_floor
AtomsGroup.desc: Height of ground floor above grade

Atom.name: MDD
Atom.desc: Different materials in the two directions

Atom.name: CLBLH
Atom.desc: Fired clay hollow blocks or tiles

Atom.name: LDD
Atom.desc: Different types of llrs in the two directions

Atom.name: LFLSINF
Atom.desc: Infilled flat slab/plate or infilled waffle slab

Atom.name: LHV
Atom.desc:
LHV(sys_a-sys_b), hybrid LLRS in height 
(a= primary system and secondary system)

Atom.name: LFC
Atom.desc: LFC:n, n is the lateral force coefficient in percentage (%)

Atom.name: DBD
Atom.desc: Equipped with base isolation and/or energy dissipation devices

Atom.name: DCW
Atom.desc:
Float specifying the density or ratio between the area of columns and/or walls and the area of the building plan.
(DCW <= 1)

Atom.name: H
Atom.desc: H:n, exact number of storeys above ground

Atom.name: HAPP
Atom.desc: HAPP:n, approximate number of storeys above ground.

Atom.name: HHT
Atom.desc: HHT:n, total height of the structure, measured from the ground floor. Float specifying the height of the structures in meters. (HHT>= 1)

Atom.name: HHI
Atom.desc: HHI:n, inter-storey height (average). Float specifying the average floor height in meters. (HHI>= 1)

Atom.name: HB
Atom.desc: HB:n, exact number of storeys below ground (same as number of basements)

Atom.name: HBAPP
Atom.desc: HBAPP:n, approximate number of storeys below ground

Atom.name: HF
Atom.desc: HF:n, exact height of ground floor level above grade

Atom.name: HFAPP
Atom.desc: HFAPP:n, approximate height of  ground floor level above grade

Atom.name: HD
Atom.desc: HD:n, slope of the ground (n=float in degrees).

Atom.name: Y
Atom.desc: Y:n, Exact date of construction or retrofit

Atom.name: YPRE
Atom.desc: YPRE:n, Latest possible date of construction or retrofit

Atom.name: YAPP
Atom.desc: YAPP:n, Approximate date of construction or retrofit

Atom.name: PLFSQO
Atom.desc: Square, with an interior opening (e.g. a "donut")

Atom.name: CHV
Atom.desc: Change in vertical structure (includes large overhangs)

Atom.name: GFO
Atom.desc: Ground floor plan fully open (no walls)

Atom.name: GFH
Atom.desc: Ground floor plan partially open (i.e. with at least 50% of walls).

Atom.name: WOL
Atom.desc: Large openings (i.e. more than 50% of the wall surface area is occupied by windows and/or doors)

Atom.name: WOM
Atom.desc: Moderate openings (i.e. from 20% to 50% of the wall surface area is occupied by windows and/or doors)

Atom.name: WOS
Atom.desc: Small openings (i.e. less than 20% of the wall surface area is occupied by windows and/or doors)

Atom.name: RM3
Atom.desc: Composite masonry and concrete roof system

Atom.name: RC3
Atom.desc: Precast concrete roof with reinforced concrete topping

Atom.name: RC4
Atom.desc: Precast concrete roof without reinforced concrete topping

Atom.name: RME1
Atom.desc: Metal or steel beams or trusses supporting light roofing

Atom.name: RME2
Atom.desc: Metal or steel beams supporting precast concrete slabs

Atom.name: RME3
Atom.desc: Composite steel deck and concrete slab

Atom.name: RWO2
Atom.desc: Wooden beams or trusses with  heavy roof covering

Atom.name: RWO3
Atom.desc: Wood-based sheets on rafters or purlins

Atom.name: RWO4
Atom.desc: Plywood panels or other light-weight panels for roof

Atom.name: RWCP
Atom.desc: Roof-wall diaphragm connection present (the connection  transfers in-plane forces from floor to wall and restrains wall outward displacements)

Atom.name: RTDP
Atom.desc: Roof tie-down present (a connection that provides vertical attachment of roof to wall in order to restrain roof from upward displacement, lift-off due to wind)

Atom.name: FN
Atom.desc: No elevated or suspended floor material (single-storey building)

Atom.name: FM3
Atom.desc: Composite cast-in-place reinforced concrete and masonry floor system

Atom.name: FC3
Atom.desc: Precast concrete floor with reinforced concrete topping

Atom.name: FC4
Atom.desc: Precast concrete floor without reinforced concrete topping

Atom.name: FME1
Atom.desc: Metal beams, trusses, or joists supporting light flooring

Atom.name: FME2
Atom.desc: Metal beams supporting precast concrete slabs

Atom.name: FME3
Atom.desc: Composite steel deck and concrete slab

Atom.name: FW1
Atom.desc: Wooden beams or trusses and joists supporting light flooring

Atom.name: FW2
Atom.desc: Wooden beams or trusses and joists supporting heavy flooring

Atom.name: FW3
Atom.desc: Wood-based sheets on joists or beams

Atom.name: FW4
Atom.desc: Plywood panels or other light-weight panels for floor

Atom.name: FWCP
Atom.desc: Floor-wall diaphragm connection present (the role of the connection is to restrain wall out-of-plane forces and to transfer in-plane forces to wall)
